 LADF05%2FHjcO%2BoZA1XvzsCU6bTEG073zBzpY13V8%3D&reserved=0>\n______________
 _______________\n\n Date updated due to a public holiday in Sri Lanka.\n__
 ___________________________\n Hi\,\nI know it feels like we've paused a bi
 t on the eMng process discussions\, but don't worry. Since last week\, we 
 have managed to align R&D and Support on the main goal.\n\nThe eManager up
 grade goal for 2025 is:\nUpgrade customers who either have critical bugs t
 hat are only fixed by upgrading to 1.53 or who are waiting for functionali
 ty that is only available in 1.53.\n\nThis goal encompasses approximately 
 60% of our customer base. The upgrades are crucial for our business and th
 e need for them is unrelated to the ESS state of development.\n\nAs you kn
 ow\, there are two primary interfaces between the Continuity team and Supp
 ort. The alignment meetings regarding new support cases and the meetings r
 egarding upgrades\, and Jon is working on building up a better alignment v
 ia both already.\n\nIn this meeting\, let's discuss improvement ideas for 
 the development process going forward. Some of the already proposed ideas 
 are:\n\n  *\nShared troubleshooting sessions between R&D and Support.\n  *
 \nUpgrade "dry-run" per customer. (Testing with customer DB before the upg
 rade is initiated.)\n  *\nLeveraging AI tools to establish automated E2E t
 est cases.\n  *\nEstablishing the acceptable cost and risk level for upgra
 ding a customer. (needs input from business leadership)\n  *\nAlignment of
  R&D and Support processes and creating close collaboration from now on.\n
 \nBest Regards\,\nTomas\n\n_______________________________________________
