DESCRIPTION:Hello all\,\n\n⚠️ Please read the agenda and decide if you 
 are impacted. We invited all developers\, but some of you might not be aff
 ected.\n\nWe’d like to invite all those developers who are working with 
 design files. The aims of this workshop are getting on the same page\, ali
 gnment\, and agreement.\n\nAgenda:\n\n  *\nIntroduction the structure of F
 igma: how to search for files\, projects themselves\, general logic across
  the files - @Oleksandr<mailto:oleksandr.spichka@elementlogic.net>\n  *\nS
 mooth navigation: introduction to the Figma file structure - pages\, auto-
 layout frames\, naming conventions\, utilizing AXON and establishing defau
 lts - @Dora<mailto:dora.makszy@elementlogic.net>\n  *\nIterations: introdu
 cing branches and how we can collaborate - @Andre<mailto:andre.nguyen@elem
 entlogic.net>\n     *\nGovernance model: at least someone from the team sh
 ould approve\, and the rest are informed in open\, clear discussions regar
 ding updates.\n  *\nDesign handover - @Dora<mailto:dora.makszy@elementlogi
 c.net>\n     *\nHow do we use the established defaults/templates?\n     *\
 nHow do we involve developers to the design process? Why and how do we rel
 y on developers’ expertise?\n  *\nDefault screen size: to have unified d
 esigns across the ecosystem\, we should agree on its relevance - @Oleksand
 r<mailto:oleksandr.spichka@elementlogic.net>\n  *\nAny other questions\, c
 oncerns?  - Developers\n\nThe discussion will be recorded. Please come pre
 pared - what we agreed on today\, will be the golden standard for ESS. If 
 you can’t join\, but have something important to say\, let us (Designers
 ) know in advance\, or trust someone to be your advocate.\n\nWe’re count
 ing on you!\n\nBest wishes\,\nThe UX team\n\n_____________________________
