DESCRIPTION:Fredrik has sent us a list of questions about how batching work
 s in eManager. Jens Erik has agreed to share what he knows. We’ll have a
  discussion and see how many of the questions we can answer. If time allow
 s way may look at some code together and/or note down some questions for f
 urther investigation.\n\nQuestions so far:\n\nHow is eManager creating bat
 ched taskgroup?\nFrom what it seems is eManager getting a number of missio
 ns to select from\, depending in the parameter PickingNumberOfMissionsToSe
 lectFromWhenCreatePickRound\nBut the rest is an unsolved mystery to me.\nL
 ets say for simplicity that we have parameter set to 100 missions\, and ba
 tch consist of 4 picklists\n\nWill eManager pair and rank those 100mission
 s or will it get the all the missions with the same extpicklistid from tha
 t he gets from the first 100missions?\n\nFurthermore\, The algorithm of pa
 ring the picklists into a batch.(?)\nDepending on the answer of the first 
 question\, how will eManager put picklists in 4 and 4 ?\nIs is those that 
 has the most matching locations? and next batch is the once with the secon
 d most matches in locations on so on?\nWhats the logic in arranging and 
 “scoring” the best matches ?\n\nIs there somthing else that is conside
 red while creating the batched picklist in the taskgroup?\nPriority? Reque
 st time? sequence?\n\n\n__________________________________________________
