DESCRIPTION:Hi everyone\,\nYou’re invited to participate in an Explorator
 y Testing session focused on ELWS Inbound Operations.\nThis session is des
 igned to leverage your experience and curiosity to uncover risks\, edge ca
 ses\, and opportunities for improvement beyond scripted testing. Rather th
 an following strict test cases\, you’ll have the freedom to explore work
 flows\, challenge assumptions\, and validate the behavior.\nScope of Explo
 ration\n\n  *\nInbound operations (receiving\, workflows\, integrations)\n
   *\nEnd-to-end behavior across UI\, APIs\, and workflows\n  *\nError hand
 ling\, data quality\, and system feedback\n\nPre-Session Checklist (Please
  Verify)\nBefore the session begins\, please make sure:\n\n  *\n✅ Testmo
  access is working and Jira integration is correctly configured\n  *\n✅ 
 Postman is installed and you can send basic API requests\n  *\n✅ ESS Too
 lkit is cloned and locally configured\n     *\nRepository: https://github.
 com/Element-Logic/ess-toolkit\n  *\n✅ Camunda credentials are configured
  and you can access Camunda Cockpit\n  *\n✅ Required services can be sta
 rted locally without error\n\nThis will help us avoid setup delays and max
 imize exploration time.\nHow to Approach the Session\n\n  *\nFollow your i
 nstincts — explore what feels risky\, unclear\, or fragile\n  *\nDocumen
 t observations\, questions\, and bugs in Testmo\n  *\nFocus on learning an
 d insight\, not just defect counts\n\nIf you have any questions before or 
 during the session\, feel free to reach out.\nLooking forward to your find
 ings and insights — this is where the really valuable feedback comes fro
 m.\nThanks\,\nRamesh Fernando\nESS QA\n\n\n_______________________________
