DESCRIPTION:Hi everyone\,\n\nThis will be a fully online planning session. 
 Please note that all times are in Norwegian time (CET).\n\nPreparations\nA
 ll teams are expected to prepare a draft plan in Jira ahead of the ELWS Pl
 anning for Iteration 4 (Kidsworld 0.5 scope/ the next two months).\nBacklo
 g Owners and PMs have already been informed and are responsible for coordi
 nating this preparation with their teams.\nThe expectation is that teams c
 ome prepared with a structured\, review-ready plan.\n\nPractical informati
 on\n\n  *   This is a fully online meeting. Please join individually – n
 o hybrid setups.\n  *   Make sure you have food\, drinks\, and snacks avai
 lable\, as breaks will be short.\n  *   Breakout sessions and online meeti
 ng room details will be shared in advance.\n\nAgenda\nThe main objective i
 s to align on dependencies\, timelines\, and risks\, and to agree on and c
 ommit to a realistic plan for the Kidsworld 0.5 scope / the next two month
 s.\n\nEach team is expected to present their planning\, covering:\n\n  *  
  Epics (in Jira Plans)\n  *   Key dependencies on other teams (in Jira Pla
 ns)\n  *   Main risks (in AirFocus – PMs have access\; please reach out 
 if support is needed)\n  *   Confidence rating (given live during the sess
 ion)\n\nPlease note that minor adjustments to the agenda may be made based
  on overall progress and alignment needs.\n\nStart time\nEnd time\nDuratio
 n\nTopic\nResponsible\n13:00\n13:05\n5 min\nIntroduction (common session)\
 nAnne H. Pedersen\,\nGard Heiaas\n13:05\n14:35\n1 h 30 min\nBreakout sessi
 ons part 1\n\n  *   Identify/discuss dependencies\, align timelines and ba
 cklog accordingly\n  *   Identify risks and mitigations connected to your 
 backlog\nAnne H. Pedersen\,\nGard Heiaas\, Backlog owners\n14:05\n14:35\n3
 0 min\nPLT risk meeting (might be in parallel with breakout sessions)\nPLT
  leadership and backlog owners\nBacklog owners\, PLT\n14:35\n14:50\n15 min
 \nBreak\n\n14:50\n15:20\n30 min\nBreakout sessions part 2\n\n  *   Identif
 y/discuss dependencies\, align timelines and backlog accordingly\n  *   Id
 entify risks and mitigations connected to your backlog\nAnne H. Pedersen\,
 \nGard Heiaas\, Backlog owners\n15:20\n16:50\n1 h 30 min\nPresentation of 
 plan and risks for iteration 4\n\n  *   Epics (in Jira Plans)\n  *   Key d
 ependencies on other teams (in Jira Plans)\n  *   Main risks (in AirFocus)
 \n  *   Confidence rating (in real time)\n\nAnne H. Pedersen\,\nGard Heiaa
 s\, Backlog owners\n16:50\n17:00\n10 min\nClosing remarks (common session)
 \nChristian Rognes\n\nLooking forward to the planning meeting with you!\n\
